category.name: games
description:
Want to play boardgames more often?
There are different groups already playing boardgames in Stockholm, and this meetup group aims to help boardgamers like yourself find out when and where they are.

• We welcome both new and experienced players, and hope everyone has fun!
• If you have a favorite game you want to play, bring it along and invite others to join you at the table.
• You can join even if you don't speak Swedish; games are often in English or language independent, and most other participants speak English if asked politely.

Meetups are organized several times per week
If you are planning to join a meetup, please RSVP so we know how many participants to expect! You can also bring friends by adding them as your +1.

Are you organizing a public boardgame event in the near future?
Are you organizing an event! Whether it's in a pub, office or someone's home -- let's get together and play =)

• Larger/recurring get-togethers are organized as meetups. Ask the admins!
• Smaller/one-time events are self-organized through the discussions/forums. Start a new thread!

Would you like to collaborate?
Do you have a new game you'd like to try out with real gamers? Want to reach over 1000 boardgamers in the Stockholm area? Join a meetup and announce your prototype in the comments, start a new thread, or ask the admins!
name: Stockholm Boardgames

description:
Gotta catch em all? Well, catch some at least....by cycle-taxi! Do you believe in making the most of summer and being sociable? Read on...

The dangers of Stockholm Pokemon Go include falling into the water, being flattened by the number 3 bus or being mowed down by an angry lycra-clad cyclist. If you value your life yet still want to have a fun evening catching Pokemon all around Stockholm city centre then let a cycle-taxi do all the work. You focus on your screen and save your little feet from endless walking and catch more Pokemon whilst the rider gets you to all the best places. Meet other players, have fun in a Hej Hej cycle-taxi and finish off catching a cold, refreshing beer at the end of it all? Sound worth trying once? Then do it!

category.name: games
description:
Welcome to the Stockholm Roleplaying Guild. 

We're a group of people who are into tabletop roleplaying games.

This meetup group is intended to allow Tabletop RPG gamers of Stockholm to find other people to game with, to join sessions hosted by it's members, and to use this page as a starting point to get your game on in the Stockholm region. 

Also, we support a number of regular campaigns, running at least one session a month, as well as one-shot adventures. Each game supports 3-6 players plus a Games Master. Anyone is welcome to join &/or run a game and coordinate via this site.

A roleplaying campaign involves playing a character over many sessions, stretching over months or sometimes even years and would suit players ready to commit to attending most sessions in order to help keep the story going and to be fair to other players.

One-shot adventures are suited to play over one or two sessions and are suitable for players interested in trying roleplaying games but who are unwilling or unable to commit to a full campaign.  They're also a good way to try out something new or take a break from your regular campaign.

We currently run one whole-club meetup a month, usually on the second Saturday of the month, in Älvsjö. The monthly meetups are a time to get everyone together in the same space to run all the games we're currently running, catch up with our fellow gamers, and briefly discuss club business. People are, of course, welcome to run their own games whenever they like and use this Meetup as a resource for getting in touch with others.

The monthly Meetups will be posted with a list of the currently available games, with the GM of each game describing what they're running, what to expect, and how to RSVP if there are any seats available for their game.

If you want to run a game at one of our meetups or anywhere else, please message one of the Admins for access.

The Admin Team:

• Jesse 

• Mark

• Christine

• Alex

• Michael

• Seyit

• Alessio 

• Magda

• Linus

--------

Roll well.

description:
You like board games (no matter the form: strategy, coop, cards...)? You wish to meet new people while doing something fun? Perhaps you want to discover new games? Or you're looking for players to try out that brand new game you just bought or to play this old one you love?

Whatever your reasons, welcome to the Göteborg Board Games Meetup!

The ambition with this group is to meet once every 2 weeks to talk about board games in all their forms and of course to play the games we like! From the classics (monopoly, chess, risk...) to the newest ones, from those that only take 30mn to those that last several hours (though for now Role Playing Games aren't the primary target but we can discuss how to make it happen if anyone is interested)!

Note that I would like the language of this group to be English, both online and during our meetings, to ensure people from every horizon can participate (and most games are in English anyway).

~~~~~~
I started this meet up because I love board games myself and know it's not always easy to find players or to know which game to buy next. Plus they're a great ice breaker and a good way to make friends!
name: Göteborg Board Games Meetup

description:
You like board games (no matter the form: strategy, coop, cards...)? You wish to meet new people while doing something fun? Perhaps you want to discover new games? Or you're looking for players to try out that brand new game you just bought or to play this old one you love?

Whatever your reasons, welcome to the Göteborg Board Games Meetup!

The ambition with this group is to meet once every 2 weeks to talk about board games in all their forms and of course to play the games we like! From the classics (monopoly, chess, risk...) to the newest ones, from those that only take 30mn to those that last several hours (though for now Role Playing Games aren't the primary target but we can discuss how to make it happen if anyone is interested)!

Note that I would like the language of this group to be English, both online and during our meetings, to ensure people from every horizon can participate (and most games are in English anyway).

~~~~~~
I started this meet up because I love board games myself and know it's not always easy to find players or to know which game to buy next. Plus they're a great ice breaker and a good way to make friends!

description:
Want to play boardgames more often?
There are different groups already playing boardgames in Stockholm, and this meetup group aims to help boardgamers like yourself find out when and where they are.

• We welcome both new and experienced players, and hope everyone has fun!
• If you have a favorite game you want to play, bring it along and invite others to join you at the table.
• You can join even if you don't speak Swedish; games are often in English or language independent, and most other participants speak English if asked politely.

Meetups are organized several times per week
If you are planning to join a meetup, please RSVP so we know how many participants to expect! You can also bring friends by adding them as your +1.

Are you organizing a public boardgame event in the near future?
Are you organizing an event! Whether it's in a pub, office or someone's home -- let's get together and play =)

• Larger/recurring get-togethers are organized as meetups. Ask the admins!
• Smaller/one-time events are self-organized through the discussions/forums. Start a new thread!

Would you like to collaborate?
Do you have a new game you'd like to try out with real gamers? Want to reach over 1000 boardgamers in the Stockholm area? Join a meetup and announce your prototype in the comments, start a new thread, or ask the admins!
name: Stockholm Boardgames

category.name: games
description:
Welcome to the Stockholm Roleplaying Guild. 

We're a group of people who are into tabletop roleplaying games.

This meetup group is intended to allow Tabletop RPG gamers of Stockholm to find other people to game with, to join sessions hosted by it's members, and to use this page as a starting point to get your game on in the Stockholm region. 

Also, we support a number of regular campaigns, running at least one session a month, as well as one-shot adventures. Each game supports 3-6 players plus a Games Master. Anyone is welcome to join &/or run a game and coordinate via this site.

A roleplaying campaign involves playing a character over many sessions, stretching over months or sometimes even years and would suit players ready to commit to attending most sessions in order to help keep the story going and to be fair to other players.

One-shot adventures are suited to play over one or two sessions and are suitable for players interested in trying roleplaying games but who are unwilling or unable to commit to a full campaign.  They're also a good way to try out something new or take a break from your regular campaign.

We currently run one whole-club meetup a month, usually on the second Saturday of the month, in Älvsjö. The monthly meetups are a time to get everyone together in the same space to run all the games we're currently running, catch up with our fellow gamers, and briefly discuss club business. People are, of course, welcome to run their own games whenever they like and use this Meetup as a resource for getting in touch with others.

The monthly Meetups will be posted with a list of the currently available games, with the GM of each game describing what they're running, what to expect, and how to RSVP if there are any seats available for their game.

If you want to run a game at one of our meetups or anywhere else, please message one of the Admins for access.

The Admin Team:

• Jesse 

• Mark

• Christine

• Alex

• Michael

• Seyit

• Alessio 

• Magda

• Linus

--------

Roll well.

description:
You like board games (no matter the form: strategy, coop, cards...)? You wish to meet new people while doing something fun? Perhaps you want to discover new games? Or you're looking for players to try out that brand new game you just bought or to play this old one you love?

Whatever your reasons, welcome to the Göteborg Board Games Meetup!

The ambition with this group is to meet once every 2 weeks to talk about board games in all their forms and of course to play the games we like! From the classics (monopoly, chess, risk...) to the newest ones, from those that only take 30mn to those that last several hours (though for now Role Playing Games aren't the primary target but we can discuss how to make it happen if anyone is interested)!

Note that I would like the language of this group to be English, both online and during our meetings, to ensure people from every horizon can participate (and most games are in English anyway).

~~~~~~
I started this meet up because I love board games myself and know it's not always easy to find players or to know which game to buy next. Plus they're a great ice breaker and a good way to make friends!
name: Göteborg Board Games Meetup

Would you like to collaborate?
Do you have a new game you'd like to try out with real gamers? Want to reach over 1000 boardgamers in the Stockholm area? Join a meetup and announce your prototype in the comments, start a new thread, or ask the admins!

category.name: games
description:
Welcome to the Stockholm Roleplaying Guild. 

We're a group of people who are into tabletop roleplaying games.

This meetup group is intended to allow Tabletop RPG gamers of Stockholm to find other people to game with, to join sessions hosted by it's members, and to use this page as a starting point to get your game on in the Stockholm region. 

Also, we support a number of regular campaigns, running at least one session a month, as well as one-shot adventures. Each game supports 3-6 players plus a Games Master. Anyone is welcome to join &/or run a game and coordinate via this site.

A roleplaying campaign involves playing a character over many sessions, stretching over months or sometimes even years and would suit players ready to commit to attending most sessions in order to help keep the story going and to be fair to other players.

One-shot adventures are suited to play over one or two sessions and are suitable for players interested in trying roleplaying games but who are unwilling or unable to commit to a full campaign.  They're also a good way to try out something new or take a break from your regular campaign.

We currently run one whole-club meetup a month, usually on the second Saturday of the month, in Älvsjö. The monthly meetups are a time to get everyone together in the same space to run all the games we're currently running, catch up with our fellow gamers, and briefly discuss club business. People are, of course, welcome to run their own games whenever they like and use this Meetup as a resource for getting in touch with others.

The monthly Meetups will be posted with a list of the currently available games, with the GM of each game describing what they're running, what to expect, and how to RSVP if there are any seats available for their game.

If you want to run a game at one of our meetups or anywhere else, please message one of the Admins for access.

The Admin Team:

• Jesse 

• Mark

• Christine

• Alex

• Michael

• Seyit

• Alessio 

• Magda

• Linus

--------

Roll well.

category.name: games
description:
Want to play boardgames more often?
There are different groups already playing boardgames in Stockholm, and this meetup group aims to help boardgamers like yourself find out when and where they are.

• We welcome both new and experienced players, and hope everyone has fun!
• If you have a favorite game you want to play, bring it along and invite others to join you at the table.
• You can join even if you don't speak Swedish; games are often in English or language independent, and most other participants speak English if asked politely.

Meetups are organized several times per week
If you are planning to join a meetup, please RSVP so we know how many participants to expect! You can also bring friends by adding them as your +1.

Are you organizing a public boardgame event in the near future?
Are you organizing an event! Whether it's in a pub, office or someone's home -- let's get together and play =)

• Larger/recurring get-togethers are organized as meetups. Ask the admins!
• Smaller/one-time events are self-organized through the discussions/forums. Start a new thread!

Would you like to collaborate?
Do you have a new game you'd like to try out with real gamers? Want to reach over 1000 boardgamers in the Stockholm area? Join a meetup and announce your prototype in the comments, start a new thread, or ask the admins!
name: Stockholm Boardgames

description:
Welcome to the Stockholm Roleplaying Guild. 

We're a group of people who are into tabletop roleplaying games.

This meetup group is intended to allow Tabletop RPG gamers of Stockholm to find other people to game with, to join sessions hosted by it's members, and to use this page as a starting point to get your game on in the Stockholm region. 

Also, we support a number of regular campaigns, running at least one session a month, as well as one-shot adventures. Each game supports 3-6 players plus a Games Master. Anyone is welcome to join &/or run a game and coordinate via this site.

A roleplaying campaign involves playing a character over many sessions, stretching over months or sometimes even years and would suit players ready to commit to attending most sessions in order to help keep the story going and to be fair to other players.

One-shot adventures are suited to play over one or two sessions and are suitable for players interested in trying roleplaying games but who are unwilling or unable to commit to a full campaign.  They're also a good way to try out something new or take a break from your regular campaign.

We currently run one whole-club meetup a month, usually on the second Saturday of the month, in Älvsjö. The monthly meetups are a time to get everyone together in the same space to run all the games we're currently running, catch up with our fellow gamers, and briefly discuss club business. People are, of course, welcome to run their own games whenever they like and use this Meetup as a resource for getting in touch with others.

The monthly Meetups will be posted with a list of the currently available games, with the GM of each game describing what they're running, what to expect, and how to RSVP if there are any seats available for their game.

If you want to run a game at one of our meetups or anywhere else, please message one of the Admins for access.

description:
You like board games (no matter the form: strategy, coop, cards...)? You wish to meet new people while doing something fun? Perhaps you want to discover new games? Or you're looking for players to try out that brand new game you just bought or to play this old one you love?

Whatever your reasons, welcome to the Göteborg Board Games Meetup!

The ambition with this group is to meet once every 2 weeks to talk about board games in all their forms and of course to play the games we like! From the classics (monopoly, chess, risk...) to the newest ones, from those that only take 30mn to those that last several hours (though for now Role Playing Games aren't the primary target but we can discuss how to make it happen if anyone is interested)!

Note that I would like the language of this group to be English, both online and during our meetings, to ensure people from every horizon can participate (and most games are in English anyway).

~~~~~~
I started this meet up because I love board games myself and know it's not always easy to find players or to know which game to buy next. Plus they're a great ice breaker and a good way to make friends!

description:
Want to play boardgames more often?
There are different groups already playing boardgames in Stockholm, and this meetup group aims to help boardgamers like yourself find out when and where they are.

• We welcome both new and experienced players, and hope everyone has fun!
• If you have a favorite game you want to play, bring it along and invite others to join you at the table.
• You can join even if you don't speak Swedish; games are often in English or language independent, and most other participants speak English if asked politely.

Meetups are organized several times per week
If you are planning to join a meetup, please RSVP so we know how many participants to expect! You can also bring friends by adding them as your +1.

Are you organizing a public boardgame event in the near future?
Are you organizing an event! Whether it's in a pub, office or someone's home -- let's get together and play =)

• Larger/recurring get-togethers are organized as meetups. Ask the admins!
• Smaller/one-time events are self-organized through the discussions/forums. Start a new thread!

Would you like to collaborate?
Do you have a new game you'd like to try out with real gamers? Want to reach over 1000 boardgamers in the Stockholm area? Join a meetup and announce your prototype in the comments, start a new thread, or ask the admins!
name: Stockholm Boardgames

category.name: games
description:
Welcome to the Stockholm Roleplaying Guild. 

We're a group of people who are into tabletop roleplaying games.

This meetup group is intended to allow Tabletop RPG gamers of Stockholm to find other people to game with, to join sessions hosted by it's members, and to use this page as a starting point to get your game on in the Stockholm region. 

Also, we support a number of regular campaigns, running at least one session a month, as well as one-shot adventures. Each game supports 3-6 players plus a Games Master. Anyone is welcome to join &/or run a game and coordinate via this site.

A roleplaying campaign involves playing a character over many sessions, stretching over months or sometimes even years and would suit players ready to commit to attending most sessions in order to help keep the story going and to be fair to other players.

One-shot adventures are suited to play over one or two sessions and are suitable for players interested in trying roleplaying games but who are unwilling or unable to commit to a full campaign.  They're also a good way to try out something new or take a break from your regular campaign.

We currently run one whole-club meetup a month, usually on the second Saturday of the month, in Älvsjö. The monthly meetups are a time to get everyone together in the same space to run all the games we're currently running, catch up with our fellow gamers, and briefly discuss club business. People are, of course, welcome to run their own games whenever they like and use this Meetup as a resource for getting in touch with others.

The monthly Meetups will be posted with a list of the currently available games, with the GM of each game describing what they're running, what to expect, and how to RSVP if there are any seats available for their game.

If you want to run a game at one of our meetups or anywhere else, please message one of the Admins for access.

The Admin Team:

• Jesse 

• Mark

• Christine

• Alex

• Michael

• Seyit

• Alessio 

• Magda

• Linus

--------

Roll well.

description:
You like board games (no matter the form: strategy, coop, cards...)? You wish to meet new people while doing something fun? Perhaps you want to discover new games? Or you're looking for players to try out that brand new game you just bought or to play this old one you love?

Whatever your reasons, welcome to the Göteborg Board Games Meetup!

The ambition with this group is to meet once every 2 weeks to talk about board games in all their forms and of course to play the games we like! From the classics (monopoly, chess, risk...) to the newest ones, from those that only take 30mn to those that last several hours (though for now Role Playing Games aren't the primary target but we can discuss how to make it happen if anyone is interested)!

Note that I would like the language of this group to be English, both online and during our meetings, to ensure people from every horizon can participate (and most games are in English anyway).

~~~~~~
I started this meet up because I love board games myself and know it's not always easy to find players or to know which game to buy next. Plus they're a great ice breaker and a good way to make friends!
name: Göteborg Board Games Meetup

description:
Want to play boardgames more often?
There are different groups already playing boardgames in Stockholm, and this meetup group aims to help boardgamers like yourself find out when and where they are.

• We welcome both new and experienced players, and hope everyone has fun!
• If you have a favorite game you want to play, bring it along and invite others to join you at the table.
• You can join even if you don't speak Swedish; games are often in English or language independent, and most other participants speak English if asked politely.

Meetups are organized several times per week
If you are planning to join a meetup, please RSVP so we know how many participants to expect! You can also bring friends by adding them as your +1.

Are you organizing a public boardgame event in the near future?
Are you organizing an event! Whether it's in a pub, office or someone's home -- let's get together and play =)

• Larger/recurring get-togethers are organized as meetups. Ask the admins!
• Smaller/one-time events are self-organized through the discussions/forums. Start a new thread!

Would you like to collaborate?
Do you have a new game you'd like to try out with real gamers? Want to reach over 1000 boardgamers in the Stockholm area? Join a meetup and announce your prototype in the comments, start a new thread, or ask the admins!
name: Stockholm Boardgames

category.name: games
description:
Welcome to the Stockholm Roleplaying Guild. 

We're a group of people who are into tabletop roleplaying games.

This meetup group is intended to allow Tabletop RPG gamers of Stockholm to find other people to game with, to join sessions hosted by it's members, and to use this page as a starting point to get your game on in the Stockholm region. 

Also, we support a number of regular campaigns, running at least one session a month, as well as one-shot adventures. Each game supports 3-6 players plus a Games Master. Anyone is welcome to join &/or run a game and coordinate via this site.

A roleplaying campaign involves playing a character over many sessions, stretching over months or sometimes even years and would suit players ready to commit to attending most sessions in order to help keep the story going and to be fair to other players.

One-shot adventures are suited to play over one or two sessions and are suitable for players interested in trying roleplaying games but who are unwilling or unable to commit to a full campaign.  They're also a good way to try out something new or take a break from your regular campaign.

We currently run one whole-club meetup a month, usually on the second Saturday of the month, in Älvsjö. The monthly meetups are a time to get everyone together in the same space to run all the games we're currently running, catch up with our fellow gamers, and briefly discuss club business. People are, of course, welcome to run their own games whenever they like and use this Meetup as a resource for getting in touch with others.

The monthly Meetups will be posted with a list of the currently available games, with the GM of each game describing what they're running, what to expect, and how to RSVP if there are any seats available for their game.

If you want to run a game at one of our meetups or anywhere else, please message one of the Admins for access.

The Admin Team:

• Jesse 

• Mark

• Christine

• Alex

• Michael

• Seyit

• Alessio 

• Magda

• Linus

--------

Roll well.

description:
Welcome to the Stockholm Roleplaying Guild. 

We're a group of people who are into tabletop roleplaying games.

This meetup group is intended to allow Tabletop RPG gamers of Stockholm to find other people to game with, to join sessions hosted by it's members, and to use this page as a starting point to get your game on in the Stockholm region. 

Also, we support a number of regular campaigns, running at least one session a month, as well as one-shot adventures. Each game supports 3-6 players plus a Games Master. Anyone is welcome to join &/or run a game and coordinate via this site.

A roleplaying campaign involves playing a character over many sessions, stretching over months or sometimes even years and would suit players ready to commit to attending most sessions in order to help keep the story going and to be fair to other players.

One-shot adventures are suited to play over one or two sessions and are suitable for players interested in trying roleplaying games but who are unwilling or unable to commit to a full campaign.  They're also a good way to try out something new or take a break from your regular campaign.

We currently run one whole-club meetup a month, usually on the second Saturday of the month, in Älvsjö. People are, of course, welcome to run their own games whenever they like and use this Meetup as a resource for getting in touch with others.

The monthly Meetups will be posted with a list of the currently available games, with the GM of each game describing what they're running, what to expect, and how to RSVP if there are any seats available for their game.

If you want to run a game at one of our meetups or anywhere else, please message one of the Admins for access.

category.name: games
description:
Want to play boardgames more often?
There are different groups already playing boardgames in Stockholm, and this meetup group aims to help boardgamers like yourself find out when and where they are.

• We welcome both new and experienced players, and hope everyone has fun!
• If you have a favorite game you want to play, bring it along and invite others to join you at the table.
• You can join even if you don't speak Swedish; games are often in English or language independent, and most other participants speak English if asked politely.

Meetups are organized several times per week
If you are planning to join a meetup, please RSVP so we know how many participants to expect! You can also bring friends by adding them as your +1.

Are you organizing a public boardgame event in the near future?
Are you organizing an event! Whether it's in a pub, office or someone's home -- let's get together and play =)

• Larger/recurring get-togethers are organized as meetups. Ask the admins!
• Smaller/one-time events are self-organized through the discussions/forums. Start a new thread!

Would you like to collaborate?
Do you have a new game you'd like to try out with real gamers? Want to reach over 1000 boardgamers in the Stockholm area? Join a meetup and announce your prototype in the comments, start a new thread, or ask the admins!
name: Stockholm Boardgames

category.name: games
description:
Welcome to the Stockholm Roleplaying Guild. 

We're a group of people who are into tabletop roleplaying games.

This meetup group is intended to allow Tabletop RPG gamers of Stockholm to find other people to game with, to join sessions hosted by it's members, and to use this page as a starting point to get your game on in the Stockholm region. 

Also, we support a number of regular campaigns, running at least one session a month, as well as one-shot adventures. Each game supports 3-6 players plus a Games Master. Anyone is welcome to join &/or run a game and coordinate via this site.

A roleplaying campaign involves playing a character over many sessions, stretching over months or sometimes even years and would suit players ready to commit to attending most sessions in order to help keep the story going and to be fair to other players.

One-shot adventures are suited to play over one or two sessions and are suitable for players interested in trying roleplaying games but who are unwilling or unable to commit to a full campaign.  They're also a good way to try out something new or take a break from your regular campaign.

We currently run one whole-club meetup a month, usually on the second Saturday of the month, in Älvsjö. The monthly meetups are a time to get everyone together in the same space to run all the games we're currently running, catch up with our fellow gamers, and briefly discuss club business. People are, of course, welcome to run their own games whenever they like and use this Meetup as a resource for getting in touch with others.

The monthly Meetups will be posted with a list of the currently available games, with the GM of each game describing what they're running, what to expect, and how to RSVP if there are any seats available for their game.

If you want to run a game at one of our meetups or anywhere else, please message one of the Admins for access.

The Admin Team:

• Jesse 

• Mark

• Christine

• Alex

• Michael

• Seyit

• Alessio 

• Magda

• Linus

--------

Roll well.

description:
You like board games (no matter the form: strategy, coop, cards...)? You wish to meet new people while doing something fun? Perhaps you want to discover new games? Or you're looking for players to try out that brand new game you just bought or to play this old one you love?

Whatever your reasons, welcome to the Göteborg Board Games Meetup!

The ambition with this group is to meet once every 2 weeks to talk about board games in all their forms and of course to play the games we like! From the classics (monopoly, chess, risk...) to the newest ones, from those that only take 30mn to those that last several hours (though for now Role Playing Games aren't the primary target but we can discuss how to make it happen if anyone is interested)!

Note that I would like the language of this group to be English, both online and during our meetings, to ensure people from every horizon can participate (and most games are in English anyway).

~~~~~~
I started this meet up because I love board games myself and know it's not always easy to find players or to know which game to buy next. Plus they're a great ice breaker and a good way to make friends!
name: Göteborg Board Games Meetup

category.name: games
description:
Want to play boardgames more often?
There are different groups already playing boardgames in Stockholm, and this meetup group aims to help boardgamers like yourself find out when and where they are.

• We welcome both new and experienced players, and hope everyone has fun!
• If you have a favorite game you want to play, bring it along and invite others to join you at the table.
• You can join even if you don't speak Swedish; games are often in English or language independent, and most other participants speak English if asked politely.

Meetups are organized several times per week
If you are planning to join a meetup, please RSVP so we know how many participants to expect! You can also bring friends by adding them as your +1.

Are you organizing a public boardgame event in the near future?
Are you organizing an event! Whether it's in a pub, office or someone's home -- let's get together and play =)

• Larger/recurring get-togethers are organized as meetups. Ask the admins!
• Smaller/one-time events are self-organized through the discussions/forums. Start a new thread!

Would you like to collaborate?
Do you have a new game you'd like to try out with real gamers? Want to reach over 1000 boardgamers in the Stockholm area? Join a meetup and announce your prototype in the comments, start a new thread, or ask the admins!
name: Stockholm Boardgames

description:
Gotta catch em all? Well, catch some at least....by cycle-taxi! Do you believe in making the most of summer and being sociable? Read on...

The dangers of Stockholm Pokemon Go include falling into the water, being flattened by the number 3 bus or being mowed down by an angry lycra-clad cyclist. If you value your life yet still want to have a fun evening catching Pokemon all around Stockholm city centre then let a cycle-taxi do all the work. You focus on your screen and save your little feet from endless walking and catch more Pokemon whilst the rider gets you to all the best places. Meet other players, have fun in a Hej Hej cycle-taxi and finish off catching a cold, refreshing beer at the end of it all? Sound worth trying once? Then do it!

category.name: games
description:
Welcome to the Stockholm Roleplaying Guild. 

We're a group of people who are into tabletop roleplaying games.

This meetup group is intended to allow Tabletop RPG gamers of Stockholm to find other people to game with, to join sessions hosted by it's members, and to use this page as a starting point to get your game on in the Stockholm region. 

Also, we support a number of regular campaigns, running at least one session a month, as well as one-shot adventures. Each game supports 3-6 players plus a Games Master. Anyone is welcome to join &/or run a game and coordinate via this site.

A roleplaying campaign involves playing a character over many sessions, stretching over months or sometimes even years and would suit players ready to commit to attending most sessions in order to help keep the story going and to be fair to other players.

One-shot adventures are suited to play over one or two sessions and are suitable for players interested in trying roleplaying games but who are unwilling or unable to commit to a full campaign.  They're also a good way to try out something new or take a break from your regular campaign.

We currently run one whole-club meetup a month, usually on the second Saturday of the month, in Älvsjö. The monthly meetups are a time to get everyone together in the same space to run all the games we're currently running, catch up with our fellow gamers, and briefly discuss club business. People are, of course, welcome to run their own games whenever they like and use this Meetup as a resource for getting in touch with others.

The monthly Meetups will be posted with a list of the currently available games, with the GM of each game describing what they're running, what to expect, and how to RSVP if there are any seats available for their game.

If you want to run a game at one of our meetups or anywhere else, please message one of the Admins for access.

The Admin Team:

• Jesse 

• Mark

• Christine

• Alex

• Michael

• Seyit

• Alessio 

• Magda

• Linus

--------

Roll well.

description:
Gotta catch em all? Well, catch some at least....by cycle-taxi! Do you believe in making the most of summer and being sociable? Read on...

The dangers of Stockholm Pokemon Go include falling into the water, being flattened by the number 3 bus or being mowed down by an angry lycra-clad cyclist. If you value your life yet still want to have a fun evening catching Pokemon all around Stockholm city centre then let a cycle-taxi do all the work. You focus on your screen and save your little feet from endless walking and catch more Pokemon whilst the rider gets you to all the best places. Meet other players, have fun in a Hej Hej cycle-taxi and finish off catching a cold, refreshing beer at the end of it all? Sound worth trying once? Then do it!

category.name: games
description:
Welcome to the Stockholm Roleplaying Guild. 

We're a group of people who are into tabletop roleplaying games.

This meetup group is intended to allow Tabletop RPG gamers of Stockholm to find other people to game with, to join sessions hosted by it's members, and to use this page as a starting point to get your game on in the Stockholm region. 

Also, we support a number of regular campaigns, running at least one session a month, as well as one-shot adventures. Each game supports 3-6 players plus a Games Master. Anyone is welcome to join &/or run a game and coordinate via this site.

A roleplaying campaign involves playing a character over many sessions, stretching over months or sometimes even years and would suit players ready to commit to attending most sessions in order to help keep the story going and to be fair to other players.

One-shot adventures are suited to play over one or two sessions and are suitable for players interested in trying roleplaying games but who are unwilling or unable to commit to a full campaign.  They're also a good way to try out something new or take a break from your regular campaign.

We currently run one whole-club meetup a month, usually on the second Saturday of the month, in Älvsjö. The monthly meetups are a time to get everyone together in the same space to run all the games we're currently running, catch up with our fellow gamers, and briefly discuss club business. People are, of course, welcome to run their own games whenever they like and use this Meetup as a resource for getting in touch with others.

The monthly Meetups will be posted with a list of the currently available games, with the GM of each game describing what they're running, what to expect, and how to RSVP if there are any seats available for their game.

If you want to run a game at one of our meetups or anywhere else, please message one of the Admins for access.

The Admin Team:

• Jesse 

• Mark

• Christine

• Alex

• Michael

• Seyit

• Alessio 

• Magda

• Linus

--------

Roll well.
